reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Title: Versatile and Stylish Storage Solution
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the WLIVE Fabric Dresser for my bedroom, and I must say, it's been a delightful addition. The dresser's white color and clean design add a touch of modern elegance to my room. With six drawers, it offers ample storage space, making it perfect for organizing clothes, accessories, and miscellaneous items.The fabric bins are surprisingly sturdy and slide in and out smoothly. They are also quite spacious, and their fabric design adds a cozy touch that would blend well with a variety of decor styles. This dresser isn't just limited to bedroom use; its versatile design makes it suitable for the living room, hallway, or even in a closet for extra organization.Assembly was relatively straightforward. The instructions were clear, and I was able to put it together by myself in about an hour. The frame feels stable and durable, though it's lightweight enough to move around if needed.My only minor gripe is that the fabric bins, while quite durable, don't have the same rigidity as wooden drawers. But considering the affordability and design of the product, this is a small concession.Overall, the WLIVE Fabric Dresser is a great purchase for anyone looking for a stylish, functional, and affordable storage solution. It's helped me keep my space organized and looking great!"

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, roomy and easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I am very happy with this dresser it was pretty easy to assemble. I did have to take a few pieces of apart and reassemble because it's hard to figure the front and the back of the dresser. Once I determined everything, it went together nicely.The drawers are roomy, easy to assemble and sturdy.I got the gray. The drawers are gray, the frame is white, the handles are white and the top is a beige linoleum. I would have preferred the top to be gray or white, although it is not obnoxious. I can live with it for the quality, value and the ease of assembly. The drawers are fabric but very sturdy. Also are easy to slide in and out. We used it in a small guest room for short-term stays it's perfect or a child's bedroom. Also a great little storage cabinet for an attic or closet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great dresser for the size and price! Perfect for a kids bedroom. It was easy to put together, just follow the directions! Very sturdy. Even the drawers are sturdy.My only complaint….. the sticker on the TOP of the board!!! Why?!? It leave a sticky residue on the very top corner!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What more could you want for $55?
reviews.reviewText: Much better quality than excepted for such a low price. Dresser is small, best suited for one person. Very light weight.Assembly is fairly quick and easy. If you have ever purchased similar types of furniture on Amazon, this should be extremely simple for you. Does take a hot minute to get things together, approx 40 minutes. The screwdriver part of the Alan wrench is terrible, use your own Phillips head screwdriver for attaching the handles to the dresser.The piece is actually pretty sturdy for the design. Once everything is set up and tightened, it doesn't wobble or anything. Better quality than excepted for sure. Same with the drawers, much more stable and thick than excepted.All in all a good piece of furniture for the price. As long as your expectations are realistic you'll be happy with this purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So nice for the price!
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this mini dresser after donating a heavy, solid wood bedroom suite of furniture to make my bedroom feel more spacious. The price caused me hesitation, as I thought it might look too cheaply made. I am so glad I decided to try it! Ble to assemble in a short amount of time with no frustration. Top is a wood based material and drawer fronts are matching wood look fabric. Yes...fabric! Very light, yet sturdy, and even comes with the attachment part for the wall if you have small children to keep it from falling on them. Metal frame is light, but plenty sturdy. Drawers are very deep - can easily hold at least 4 bulky sweaters per drawer. I would think it would be the perfect purchase for student apartments, anyone living in a small apartment or home, guestroom, or even to add drawer space in a closet. Don't let the price hold you back from seeing what a terrific, useful little dresser this is!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I needed something slim sturdy & inexpensive to hold clothes and use the top for toilettes and whatever for guests. I thought crates would do it but they are astronomical $. This fit right in the closet no problem. Quick put together Can be done by one but more fun with 2. It has the option to secure to the wall but hubby said no way Its a good value for the $

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Dresser is Super Small
reviews.reviewText: My family was making fun of me on how small this dresser is. My oldest has a dresser like this and it's much bigger. I was expecting it to be like that. And by the pictures and video you would expect it to be a good size. It's really not. It maybe comes up to my hip. I'll probably give this to my kid for her room. My laundry bag is taller.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Inexpensive yet functional solution for a small child’s room
reviews.reviewText: We bought this dresser for my 8-year-old stepson’s clothes. We set it up last night.The only complaint so far is that the package we received was obviously a return. Thankfully, all parts were included.It’s a good size for a smaller bedroom, and it isn’t too tall, so he’ll easily be able to reach the top. My stepson has a very small wardrobe, and I suspect we’ll need to get something a bit bigger when he’s older.Quality-wise, it feels sturdy without being too heavy. The drawers slide easily. The material of the drawers is a sturdy canvas, and it has the appearance of real wood without the cost/weight. I am happy with how it looks.I would recommend this dresser for a relatively inexpensive but nice-looking and functional solution for a smaller bedroom and child.
